  144. ‌let format_backtrace_slot pos slot =
  145.   let info is_raise =
  146.     if is_raise then
  147.       if pos = 0 then "Raised at" else "Re-raised at"
  148.     else
  149.       if pos = 0 then "Raised by primitive operation at" else "Called from"
  150.   in
  151.   match slot with
  152.   | Unknown_location l ->
  153.       if l.is_raise then
  154.         (* compiler-inserted re-raise, skipped *) None
  155.       else
  156.         Some (sprintf "%s unknown location" (info false))
  157.   | Known_location l ->
  158.       Some (sprintf "%s %s in file \"%s\"%s, line %d, characters %d-%d"
  159.               (info l.is_raise) l.defname l.filename
  160.               (if l.is_inline then " (inlined)" else "")
  161.               l.line_number l.start_char l.end_char)

  163. ‌let print_exception_backtrace outchan backtrace =
  164.   match backtrace with
  165.   | None ->
  166.       fprintf outchan
  167.         "(Program not linked with -g, cannot print stack backtrace)\n"
  168.   | Some a ->
  169.       for i = 0 to Array.length a - 1 do
  170.         match format_backtrace_slot i a.(i) with
  171.           | None -> ()
  172.           | Some str -> fprintf outchan "%s\n" str
  173.       done

  182. ‌let backtrace_to_string backtrace =
  183.   match backtrace with
  184.   | None ->
  185.      "(Program not linked with -g, cannot print stack backtrace)\n"
  186.   | Some a ->
  187.       let b = Buffer.create 1024 in
  188.       for i = 0 to Array.length a - 1 do
  189.         match format_backtrace_slot i a.(i) with
  190.           | None -> ()
  191.           | Some str -> bprintf b "%s\n" str
  192.       done;
  193.       Buffer.contents b

  228. ‌let backtrace_slots raw_backtrace =
  229.   (* The documentation of this function guarantees that Some is
  230.      returned only if a part of the trace is usable. This gives us
  231.      a bit more work than just convert_raw_backtrace, but it makes the
  232.      API more user-friendly -- otherwise most users would have to
  233.      reimplement the "Program not linked with -g, sorry" logic
  234.      themselves. *)
  235.   match convert_raw_backtrace raw_backtrace with
  236.     | None -> None
  237.     | Some backtrace ->
  238.       let usable_slot = function
  239.         | Unknown_location _ -> false
  240.         | Known_location _ -> true in
  241.       let rec exists_usable = function
  242.         | (-1) -> false
  243.         | i -> usable_slot backtrace.(i) || exists_usable (i - 1) in
  244.       if exists_usable (Array.length backtrace - 1)
  245.       then Some backtrace
  246.       else None

  248. ‌let backtrace_slots_of_raw_entry entry =
  249.   backtrace_slots [| entry |]

  315. ‌let default_uncaught_exception_handler exn raw_backtrace =
  316.   eprintf "Fatal error: exception %s\n" (to_string exn);
  317.   print_raw_backtrace stderr raw_backtrace;
  318.   let status = get_debug_info_status () in

  335. ‌let handle_uncaught_exception' exn debugger_in_use =
  336.   try
  337.     (* Get the backtrace now, in case one of the [at_exit] function
  338.        destroys it. *)
  339.     let raw_backtrace =
  340.       if debugger_in_use (* Same test as in [runtime/printexc.c] *) then
  341.         empty_backtrace
  342.       else
  343.         try_get_raw_backtrace ()
  344.     in
  345.     (try Stdlib.do_at_exit () with _ -> ());
  346.     try
  347.       !uncaught_exception_handler exn raw_backtrace
  348.     with exn' ->
  349.       let raw_backtrace' = try_get_raw_backtrace () in
  350.       eprintf "Fatal error: exception %s\n" (to_string exn);
  351.       print_raw_backtrace stderr raw_backtrace;
  352.       eprintf "Fatal error in uncaught exception handler: exception %s\n"
  353.         (to_string exn');
  354.       print_raw_backtrace stderr raw_backtrace';
  355.       flush stderr
  356.   with
  357.     | Out_of_memory ->
  358.         prerr_endline
  359.           "Fatal error: out of memory in uncaught exception handler"

  361. (* This function is called by [caml_fatal_uncaught_exception] in
